{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# 01 — Linear analysis with mochi\n\nThis notebook walks through the bread-and-butter linear-control workflow on a few single-block plants:\n\n1. **RLCircuit** — load, linearise, step/impulse, transfer function.\n2. **DCMotor** — fast/slow eigenvalues; pole-zero map.\n3. **DoubleTank** — cascaded states.\n4. **Symbolic state-space + composition** — `mod_state_space_symbolic`, `mod_transfer_function`, and `mod_cascade` to wire two RLCs into a 4-state composite.\n\nEverything here uses the linearisation around an operating point. For nonlinear simulation see `03_nonlinear.macnb`.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Load the package and helpers. */\nload(\"../../mochi.mac\")$\nload(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$\n\n/* Pole locations (eigenvalues of A) — used in scatter plots below. */\npoles_of(A_) := block([evals, _, lst],\n  [evals, _] : np_eig(ndarray(float(A_))),\n  lst : np_to_list(evals),\n  [map(realpart, lst), map(imagpart, lst)])$\n",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 37,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 1. RLC circuit\n\nA series RLC driven by a voltage source. States: inductor current $i_L$, capacitor voltage $v_C$.\nOutput: capacitor voltage.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "m_rlc : mod_load(\"../RLCircuit.mo\")$\nmod_print(m_rlc)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 38,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Model:  RLCircuit\n  parameters:  [[R,1.0],[L,0.5],[Ccap,1.0]]\n  states:      [iL,vC]\n  derivs:      [der_iL,der_vC]\n  inputs:      [Vin]\n  outputs:     [y]\n  initial:     [[iL,0],[vC,0]]\n  residuals:\n     vC+R*iL+L*der_iL-Vin  = 0\n     Ccap*der_vC-iL  = 0\n     y-vC  = 0"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Linearise at the equilibrium $i_L = v_C = V_{in} = 0$:",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "[A, B, C, D] : mod_state_space(m_rlc, [iL = 0, vC = 0, Vin = 0])$\nprint(\"A =\")$ A;\nprint(\"B =\")$ B;\nprint(\"C =\")$ C;\nprint(\"D =\")$ D;",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 39,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "A =\nmatrix([-2.0,-2.0],[1.0,0.0])\nB =\nmatrix([2.0],[0.0])\nC =\nmatrix([0.0,1.0])\nD ="
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi 0.0\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 39,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Step response",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "[t_sim, y_rlc] : mod_step(m_rlc, [iL = 0, vC = 0, Vin = 0], 14.95,\n                          ['dt = 0.05])$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=2, name=\"vC(t)\",\n  lines(t_sim, y_rlc),\n  color=\"black\", dash=\"dot\", explicit(1, t, 0, last(t_sim)),\n  title=\"RLC step response (default R=1, L=0.5, C=1)\",\n  xlabel=\"Time (s)\", ylabel=\"vC\",\n  grid=true, showlegend=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 40,
