    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 4. New API: symbolic SS, transfer function, interconnection\n\nThe package also exposes:\n\n- `mod_state_space_symbolic(m, op)` — A, B, C, D with parameters left as symbols.\n- `mod_transfer_function(m, op)` — H(s) = C(sI − A)⁻¹B + D.\n- `mod_cascade(SS1, SS2)` / `mod_parallel(SS1, SS2)` / `mod_unity_feedback(SS, K)` — block-stack two state-space tuples.\n- `mod_simulate(m, op, u_fn, t_end)` — generic input-driven simulation; `mod_step`, `mod_impulse` are wrappers.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Symbolic state-space — useful for inspecting structure */\n[As, Bs, Cs, Ds] : mod_state_space_symbolic(m_rlc, [iL = 0, vC = 0, Vin = 0])$\nprint(\"Symbolic A:\")$ As;\nprint(\"Symbolic B:\")$ Bs;",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 51,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Symbolic A:\nmatrix([-(R/L),-(1/L)],[1/Ccap,0])\nSymbolic B:"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi {{1}\\over{L}}\\cr 0\\cr \\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 51,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Transfer function */\nH_rlc : mod_transfer_function(m_rlc, [iL = 0, vC = 0, Vin = 0])$\nprint(\"H(s) =\")$ H_rlc;\nprint(\"(closed form: 1 / (LCs² + RCs + 1) = 1 / (0.5 s² + s + 1))\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 52,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "rat: replaced 2.0 by 2/1 = 2.0\nrat: replaced 2.0 by 2/1 = 2.0\nrat: replaced 2.0 by 2/1 = 2.0\nH(s) =\nmatrix([2/(s^2+2*s+2)])\n(closed form: 1 / (LCs² + RCs + 1) = 1 / (0.5 s² + s + 1))"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Cascade two RLCs and plot the impulse response of the 4-state composite */\nSS_rlc : mod_state_space(m_rlc, [iL = 0, vC = 0, Vin = 0])$\n[Ac, Bc, Cc, Dc] : mod_cascade(SS_rlc, SS_rlc)$\nprint(\"Cascade A is\", length(Ac), \"x\", length(Ac), \"(2+2 states):\")$\nAc;",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 53,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Cascade A is 4 x 4 (2+2 states):"
          ]
        },
        {
          "data": {
            "text/latex": [
              "\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined\\pmatrix{\\else\\begin{pmatrix}\\fi -2.0&-2.0&0&0\\cr1.0&0.0&0&0\\cr 0.0&2.0&-2.0&-2.0\\cr 0.0&0.0&1.0&0.0\\cr\\ifx\\endpmatrix\\undefined}\\else\\end{pmatrix}\\fi "
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 53,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Impulse response of the RLC */\n[t_imp, y_imp] : mod_impulse(m_rlc, [iL = 0, vC = 0, Vin = 0], 8.0)$\nax_draw2d(\n  color=\"blue\", line_width=2, name=\"impulse response\",\n  lines(t_imp, y_imp),\n  color=\"black\", dash=\"dot\", explicit(0, t, 0, last(t_imp)),\n  title=\"RLC impulse response\",\n  xlabel=\"Time (s)\", ylabel=\"vC(t)\",\n  grid=true, showlegend=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 54,
      "outputs": [
        {
